node.text:
With @garrettderderian: Week of August 9
—
In Manhattan, there were 333 contracts signed last week, a 42% increase from the same week in 2019, and a 164% increase from 2020.
—
In Brooklyn, there were 177 contracts signed last week, a 36% increase from the same week in 2019, and a 34% increase from 2020.
—
36 4M+ contracts were signed last week in Manhattan.

node.text:
Introducing this designer penthouse co-op with a trio of terraces and a prime Midtown location, a gut-renovated masterpiece of contemporary city luxury. 
—
Features of this one-of-a-kind home include beautiful herringbone hardwood floors, airy tray ceilings, custom lighting and built-ins, integrated audio/visual systems, oversized windows, northern and western exposure, a gas-burning fireplace, an outdoor shower, and a laundry room with custom storage, a utility sink, and an Electrolux washer/dryer. 
—
200 East 57th Street, PHB • 2 Beds • 2.5 Baths • 2,560 SF • $5,475,000
—
Repped by @seanjadidian @ryanserhant

node.text:
Doubling Manor, one of the true Greenwich Great Estates, a unique architectural style inspired by European mansions of the eighteenth and nineteenth centuries with commensurate size and scale at over 10,000 square feet with 11 bedrooms and 9.2 baths and separate guest home. 
—
Remarkably bright and airy accommodation, this estate is the best of its class. Nestled in the heart of mid-country Greenwich, overlooking perfect vistas of beautifully landscaped 6.5 acres abutting Greenwich Country Club. Luxury outdoor amenities throughout the sprawling lower lawns including incredible oversized terrace, custom pool with spa and fountain features, fishing pond, and various sports courts including tennis/basketball, volleyball and shuffleboard. 
—
25 Doubling Road • $9,995,000
—
Repped by @ryanserhant @danielle___malloy @jessica_nest_seekers @nestseekers

node.text:
Located at the sought after Shephard Condominium in the heart of the West Village, this corner home is flooded with light and boasts Hudson River views from every room. Imagine the sunsets bouncing off the water while passing by one of the many oversized windows in the 36 ft long Great Room.
—
Features include custom Lutron lighting and sun shades/window treatments controlled by Savant in all rooms, auto-lighting added to closets, custom AV sound system throughout controlled by Savant, soundproofing in walls, California closets throughout and a walk-in laundry room you can sit back, relax, and just enjoy the view.
—
275 West 10th Street, 7E • 3 Beds • 3.5 Baths • 3,160 SF • $9,999,000 
—
Repped by @ryanserhant @scottmfrancis @sara_gore

node.text:
Welcome to this one-of-a-kind floor-through co-op in Flatiron, a gut-renovated masterpiece that exemplifies contemporary city luxury and charm.
—
Features of the home include key-locked elevator access, beautiful wide oak hardwood floors, all new oversized industrial casement windows with northern and southern exposure, a home office, a gas-burning fireplace, a laundry room with a washer/dryer and utility sink, and prewar details like soaring 12-ft beamed ceilings, a riveted steel column, and exposed redbrick walls.
—
6 West 20th Street, 4 • 3 Beds • 4 Baths • $8,200,000
—

node.text:
@101west14th is an intriguing new development situated at the nexus of Chelsea and Greenwich Village. 
—
A collaboration between developer, Gemini Rosemont, and architect, ODA, the building possesses a bold stacked façade and homes with high-end fixtures and finishes. 
—
Amenities include a state-of-the-art gym, a private lounge, a lush courtyard, a full-time doorman, private storage, and a stunning rooftop deck with lounge furniture, an outdoor kitchen, and incredible views of the city skyline.
—
Repped by @ryanserhant @jen_alese @courtneytravin @scottfava @nestseekers

With @garrettderderian: Week of July 26
—
In Manhattan, there were 339 contracts signed last week, a 58% increase from the same week in 2019, and a 140% increase from 2020.
—
In Brooklyn, there were 212 contracts signed last week, an 39% increase from the same week in 2019, and a 39% increase from 2020.
—
39 4M+ contracts were signed last week in Manhattan, six more than last week!

node.text:
A lovely corner co-op nestled in the heart of the Upper East Side, this  home is a paradigm of classic city living. 
—
Features of the apartment include beamed ceilings, sash windows, northern, southern and eastern exposure, beautiful hardwood floors, new crown molding, custom A/C covers, Nest capability, and custom closets. Several upgrades like skim coated walls and a new electrical box have also been made.
—
179 East 79th Street, 11B • 1 Bed • 1 Bath • $875,000
—
Repped by @nilelundgren @samirvogan @stevenmarvin

—
Repped by @ryanserhant @nathanpfrank @nestseekers

node.text:
With @garrettderderian: Week of July 19
—
In Manhattan, there were 333 contracts signed last week, a 45% increase from the same week in 2019, and a 79% increase from 2020.
—
In Brooklyn, there were 227 contracts signed last week, a 48% increase from the same week in 2019, and a 92% increase from 2020.
—
33 4M+ contracts were signed last week in Manhattan, 5 more than last week. 23 out of the last 24 weeks registered 30+ $4M+ contracts!
—
Our Signature Report received strong press last week (links below to share), as did our Q2 South Florida Report.

node.text:
SERHANT. Signature: 24 West 10th Street
—
A magnificent 6-story townhome on one of Manhattan’s most coveted blocks, along the Gold Coast of Greenwich Village. 
—
24 West 10th Street is a one-of-a-kind, superbly renovated residence, with soaring ceilings reaching nearly 13.5 feet, grand living and entertaining spaces, a sunny South-facing garden, front garden, and tranquil rooftop terrace with skyline views. 
—
The interior has a stunning blend of restored original details and state-of-the-art upgrades. Surrounded by low landmarked townhouses, dazzling sunlight and Village views are enjoyed throughout the home, enhanced by soaring ceilings on every level. 
—
24 West 10th Street • 7 Beds • 7.5 Baths • 9,000 SF • $28,000,000
—
Repped by @ryanserhant @_nicolepalermo

node.text:
This year, our CEO & Founder, @RyanSerhant is the 2021 National Ambassador for the Real Men Wear Pink campaign to help fight breast cancer with @AmericanCancerSociety.
—
Breast cancer has just become one of the most diagnosed cancers in the world. We need to fight it, and we all know when it comes to cancer, it can’t be fought by one person alone.
—
We are asking our fellow fathers, husbands, sons, friends to join @RyanSerhant and @SERHANT in committing to wear pink everyday this October to raise awareness and funds.
—
Please head to the link in bio to nominate yourself, someone, or a local community leader to be an ambassador. The more we fight breast cancer now, the fewer women will have to fight and face it in the future.
—
Please join us, and let’s do this together!
—
#serhantwearspink #americancancersociety #ACS #breastcancer

node.text:
SERHANT. Signature: 111 Meeting House Road • $16,500,000
—
A once-in-a-lifetime Hamptons estate that redefines luxury and tranquility. Designed by award-winning firms, Bruce Nagel + Partners and Pembrooke & Ives, this turn-key residence blends scintillating outdoor space with plush interiors that speak to the opulence and charm of prime Hamptons living. 
—
A gated entrance and motor court driveway leads into four acres of Ed Hollander-landscaped property that encircles a colossal 22,238 sq. ft. mansion and a 1,500 sq. ft. carriage house. 
—
Interiors have a total of 11 bedrooms, 13 full bathrooms, and 9 half-bathrooms, while the outdoor space is punctuated by old growth trees, expansive lawns, a Gunite pool, and an adjacent deck and pavilion with shaded lounge space, changing rooms, and a kitchenette.
—
111 Meeting House Road • 11 Beds • 13 Baths • 9 Half Baths • $16,500,000
—
Repped @shawn.p.egan @ryanserhant

—
Features of this one-of-a-kind home include beautiful herringbone hardwood floors, airy tray ceilings, custom lighting and built-ins, integrated audio/visual systems, oversized windows, northern and western exposure, a gas-burning fireplace, an outdoor shower, and a laundry room with custom storage, a utility sink, and an Electrolux washer/dryer. 
—
200 East 57th Street, PHB • 2 Beds • 2.5 Baths • 2,560 SF • $5,475,000
—
Repped by @seanjadidian @ryanserhant

Just Sold: 26 East 63rd Street, PHB • Last Ask $9,999,000
—
A palatial duplex penthouse boasting a rooftop solarium and designer fixtures and finishes, this one-of-a-kind condo is a paragon of contemporary Lenox Hill luxury. 
—
Features of this incredible living space, gorgeous herringbone hardwood floors, airy 9 to 11 ft. ceilings, tasteful crown molding, chic built-ins and archways, large sash windows with northern, southern, and western exposure, central heating and cooling, a gas-burning fireplace, a convenient in-unit washer/dryer, and 800 sq. ft. of private outdoor space with breathtaking Central Park and skyline views.
—
26 East 63rd Street, PHB • 5 Beds • 5.5 Baths • 3,700 SF • Last Ask $9,999,000
—
Repped by @ryanserhant @mike_fabbri @nestseekers

Just Sold: 21 East 61st Street, 16B • Last Ask $15,500,000
—
A collaborative effort by world renowned designers Tony Ingrao and Robert Couturier has created a trophy residence atop the Carlton House featuring wrap-around terraces, high ceilings, views of Central Park plus mesmerizing city skyline views sure to take one’s breath away. 
—
With approximately 3,600 interior square feet and over 1,100 square feet of terraces, the apartment has an enormous living room over 33 feet in length plus a formal dining room large enough for the grandest sit-down entertaining. 
—
21 East 61st Street, 16B • 4 Beds • 3.5 Baths • Last Ask $15,500,000
—
Buyer repped by @chaselandow

node.text:
Welcome home, Nicole Palermo!
—
@_nicolepalermo is a highly accomplished real estate agent with nearly a decade of experience and over a half-billion dollars in sales in Manhattan’s condo, co-op, and townhouse markets. 
—
Nicole possesses extensive knowledge of market trends, and has a keen eye for design and creative marketing. As a homeowner on the famed Greenwich Village Gold Coast, she has a deep understanding of every aspect of the buying and selling process, from competitive pricing analysis and DOB regulations, to staging and renovation projects.
